sequenceDiagram
    participant browser
    participant server

    browser->>server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note
    activate server
    server-->>browser: 302 Found (redirect to /notes)
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser navigates to the notes page

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/notes
    activate server
    server-->>browser: HTML document
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser displays the notes page

    browser->>server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note
    activate server
    server-->>browser: 302 Found (redirect to /notes)
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser refreshes the notes page to display the new note

sequenceDiagram
    participant browser
    participant server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/notes
    activate server
    server-->>browser: HTML document
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the css file
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.js
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the JavaScript file
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser starts executing the JavaScript code that fetches the JSON from the server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
    activate server
    server-->>browser: [{ "content": "HTML is easy", "date": "2023-1-1" }, ... ]
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser executes the callback function that renders the notes

@startuml MortalKombatERD

!define ENTITY entity
!define PK primary key
!define FK foreign key

!define SinglePlayer <<Mode>>
!define ClassicTowers <<Mode>>
!define StoryMode <<Mode>>
!define Customize <<Mode>>

!define Kombat <<SpecialMoveCategory>>
!define Classic <<SpecialMoveCategory>>
!define Fatality <<SpecialMoveCategory>>
!define Brutality <<SpecialMoveCategory>>

entity Game {
  Name PK
  Platforms
}

entity Character {
  ID PK
  Name
  Modes
  World
  SpecialMoves
}

entity Mode {
  Type PK
}

entity Battleground {
  Name PK
  Location
  Artifacts
}

entity Fight {
  ID PK
  Battleground FK
  Game FK
  Winner FK
  Loser FK
  FixedTime
}

entity SpecialMove {
  ID PK
  Name
  Category
  Pattern
}

entity Mode {
  Type PK
}

entity GamePackage {
  Name PK
  Features
  Platform
}

entity DLC {
  Name PK
  Moves
  Costumes
  Characters
}

entity Player {
  ID PK
  Name
}

entity Tournament {
  ID PK
  StartDate
  PlayersParticipating
  Rounds
  Winner FK
  RunnerUp FK
  FinalFightDate
}

entity Round {
  ID PK
  Tournament FK
  Winner FK
  RunnerUp FK
}

Game --|{ Character
Character --{ SpecialMove
Game --|{ Mode
Battleground --|{ Fight
Game --|{ GamePackage
Game --|{ DLC
GamePackage --|{ GamePackageSales
Tournament --|{ Round
Tournament }|{ Player
Round --|{ Fight

@enduml
